{
  "stem": "2067.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We exported hazelnuts and almonds and Spanish wine to Holland and Belgium, and imported Dutch and Belgian eggs.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In 1937, my father started ailing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He had asthma and he had a stomach ailment.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we, the family, thought the time had come that my parents leave war-torn Spain.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Medicine was not easily available anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The hospitals were poor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There were not enough doctors.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "None whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had for-- for close to 500 years seen no Jews anymore, so they didn't even know what Jews were.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there was no anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We still had the German passports.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And traveling to any country in the world had become extremely difficult for-- for Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody wanted them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But Holland was the only Western-- Western European country that did not require that a visa-- a visa for Germans.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So that's why we went to Holland with my father.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I went with my parents and established them there, find a-- found a rented-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] not apartment, but a couple of rooms where they could stay, and I returned to Spain.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But six month later, it was the beginning of 1938 already, I got a telegram from my mother that my father was in serious condition in hospital and she needed help.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I left Spain, which was difficult, very difficult in those days already, and returned to Holland, and stayed there, together with my mother until my father recuperated.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I tried to-- I set up an office in Amsterdam, after I had rented an apartment for my parents, and tried to do business with my brother, the business I mentioned before, which we could do until the-- the summer of 1939.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Civil War had ended in Spain.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
